The new Board of Trustees (BoT) of the Muslim Ummah of South West Nigeria – MUSWEN, inaugurated on Saturday, May 25, 2024 at its Secretariat, 46, Iwo Road, Ibadan, has elected Dr. Abdur Rauf Bolanle Olawale Babalakin as its Chairman.

The inauguration of the Board of Trustees was perforned by the President of MUSWEN, Alhaji Rasaki Oladejo, FCS.

Immediately after inauguration, the BoT held its first meeting, which was attended by members, both physically and virtually and unanimously elected Dr. Abdur Rauf Bolanle Olawale Babalakin OFR, SAN as its Chairman.

The 9-Member Board of Trustees, made up of 7 Males and 2 Females, were chosen from across all the 6 States in the South West Zone of Nigeria (Ekiti, Lagos, Ogun, Ondo, Osun and Oyo).

Members of the Board of Trustees:

1. Dr. Abdur Rauf Bolanle Olawale Babalakin OFR, SAN;

2. Alhaja Lateefah Modupeola Okunnu, OFR;

3. Mr. Tajudeen Fola Adeola, OFR, mni;

4. Otunba Olalekan Belo

5. Mallam (Prof.) Yusuf Olaolu Ali, SAN;

6. Dr (Mrs.) Habibat Omolara Adubiaro, Secretary to Ekiti State Government;

7. His Royal Majesty, Oba Engr. Masoud Aweda Oyekola Lawal, Arowoduye II, The Iba of Kisi, Oyo State;

8. Alhaji Abdul Ganiyu Adebiyi;

9. Barrister Kazeem Olanrewaju

Prof. Muslih ‘Tayo Yahya, FAR, FASN

Executive Secretary/CEO

Muslim Ummah of South West Nigeria
